-- CANADA RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Augusta Resource, Mosaic Capital, Timmins Gold 
-- 
-- Tue Jun 24, 2014 02:50AM EDT
-- None



June 24 (Reuters) - Securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several Canadian companies, including Augusta Resource, Mosaic Capital and Timmins Gold, on Tuesday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Augusta Resource <AZC.TO>: Canaccord Genuity cuts to hold from speculative buy  * Pason Systems <PSI.TO>: National Bank Financial starts with outperform * Waterfurnace Renewable Energy <WFI.TO>: Canaccord Genuity cuts to hold from buy  Following is a summary of research actions on Canadian companies reported by Reuters on Tuesday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order. * Augusta Resource <AZC.TO>: Canaccord Genuity cuts to hold from speculative buy  * Mosaic Capital <M.V>: Canaccord Genuity raises target price to C$15 from C$14.25; buy * Painted Pony Petroleum <PPY.TO>: Canaccord Genuity raises target price to C$22 from C$18 * Pason Systems <PSI.TO>: National Bank Financial starts with outperform; target price C$35  * SNC-Lavalin Group <SNC.TO>: National Bank Financial raises target price to C$65 from C$60 * Timmins Gold <TMM.TO>: Dundee Capital raises target price to C$2.25 from C$2; rating buy * Torex Gold Resources <TXG.TO>: BMO ups target to C$2.25 from C$2;outperform (speculative) * Transition Therapeutics <TTH.TO>: Canaccord Genuity cuts target price to C$11 from C$13.25 * Waterfurnace Renewable Energy <WFI.TO>: Canaccord Genuity cuts to hold from buy